  "skeletons": {
    "results_md": "## R28 \u00b7 Geometry auxiliary-construction repair \u2014 [SLOT: verdict headline \u2014 write it from the numbers below]\n\nPopulation: 2D pruned distance-geometry chains the reference pipeline (scipy LM, k_refine=4) fails as posed under two independent restart streams; each arm's chosen construction gets one more reference solve on a fresh common stream (`run_geo_repair.py`).  Data seed 20260722 is shared across optimization seeds 11/29/47, so the failure pools coincide; flip rates are mean \u00b1 population SD over the 3 seeds.  Labels and flips are budget-relative measurements at the reference budget \u2014 NOT CAS certificates; do not reuse R10's certificate language here.\n\n| arm | trained-k (N=367) | transfer-k (N=331) |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| ranker | 0.246 \u00b1 0.016 | 0.183 \u00b1 0.007 |\n| recipe_only | 0.249 \u00b1 0.005 | 0.192 \u00b1 0.005 |\n| random | 0.185 \u00b1 0.019 | 0.140 \u00b1 0.014 |\n| best_fixed | 0.259 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.193 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| all_cos | 0.210 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.154 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| restart_control | 0.270 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.215 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| restart_plus16 | 0.572 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.514 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| restart_plus32 | 0.725 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.686 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| probe | 0.698 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.680 \u00b1 0.000 |\n| enumeration | 0.692 \u00b1 0.000 | 0.616 \u00b1 0.000 |\n\nPaired comparisons \u2014 exact McNemar on the common e2e stream, primary seed 11, Holm-corrected within each pool over the declared 6-comparison family; the other seeds are raw-p robustness columns:\n\n| ranker vs | trained W/L | trained p (Holm) | transfer W/L | transfer p (Holm) | raw p, other seeds (trained) |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| restart_control | 8/13 | 1.000 | 4/16 | 1.000 | 1.000 (s29), 0.857 (s47) |\n| random | 35/8 | 1.26e-04 | 24/8 | 0.021 | 0.284 (s29), 2.56e-06 (s47) |\n| recipe_only | 11/10 | 1.000 | 4/11 | 1.000 | 0.971 (s29), 0.154 (s47) |\n| best_fixed | 14/15 | 1.000 | 6/11 | 1.000 | 0.995 (s29), 0.572 (s47) |\n| all_cos | 35/18 | 0.068 | 16/8 | 0.379 | 0.271 (s29), 0.010 (s47) |\n| probe | 10/172 | 1.000 | 12/178 | 1.000 | 1.000 (s29), 1.000 (s47) |\n\nCost (restarts per instance, mean over seeds): ranker 4.0, probe 19.5, restart_plus32 32.0, enumeration 72.7.\n\nLabel-vs-e2e agreement proxy (seed 11, all 698 test rows): \"label stream found \u22651 working construction\" vs \"enumeration flipped on the e2e stream\" agree on 480/698 = 0.688 [0.652,0.721] (label+/e2e\u2212 48, label\u2212/e2e+ 170).  Random-arm calibration: flip 0.158 vs 0.106 expected from mean(n_working/n_candidates).  Per-candidate top1-hit agreement is not derivable from the stored rows; rerun with the per-candidate label vector stored per row to get it.\n\nEvidence: results/p_geo_repair/geo_repair_s{11,29,47}.json, results/p_geo_repair/analysis.json.\n[SLOT: PROVENANCE row \u2014 command, seeds, commit]",
    "marc_tex": "% --- R28 geometry construction repair (generated by analyze_geo_repair.py; verify before pasting) ---\nOn pruned distance-geometry chains the reference pipeline fails as posed (two independent restart streams; $N=367$ trained-$k$, $N=331$ held-out-$k$ failures), the construction ranker flips $0.246 \\pm 0.016$ of the trained-$k$ pool at one augmented reference solve, against $0.270 \\pm 0.000$ for the matched-budget restart control and $0.572 \\pm 0.000$/$0.725 \\pm 0.000$ at $+16$/$+32$ restarts; the no-learning construction arms reach $0.259 \\pm 0.000$ (best fixed), $0.210 \\pm 0.000$ (all cosine lifts) and $0.249 \\pm 0.005$ (recipe-only ranker).\nExact paired McNemar tests on the common stream, Holm-corrected over the six-comparison family, give p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 1.000, 0.857) against the restart control, p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.995, 0.572) against best-fixed and p=0.068 (raw p other seeds: 0.271, 0.010) against all-cos on the primary seed (seeds 11/29/47, mean $\\pm$ population SD).\nThe probe control reaches $0.698 \\pm 0.000$ at 19.5 restarts per instance versus the ranker's 4.0, and enumeration bounds the ceiling at $0.692 \\pm 0.000$ at 72.7.\nOn the held-out-$k$ pool the ranker flips $0.183 \\pm 0.007$ versus $0.215 \\pm 0.000$ for the restart control (p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.961, 0.999)) and $0.193 \\pm 0.000$ for best-fixed (p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.581, 0.928)).\nLabels and flips are budget-relative measurements at the reference-solver budget, not certificates.\n[SLOT: claim sentence \u2014 write only after checking the ranker-vs-best\\_fixed/all\\_cos direction; if a fixed construction is competitive, report it as the honest ceiling.]"
